1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 1st Session of the 60th Legislature (2025)
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to marriage and family; enacting 43
O.S. Section 115.1, which relates to child support;
8 establishing penalties for failure to pay child
support; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 115.1 of Title 43, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 Section 115.1. A. Civil actions for failure to pay child
16 support may be brought by the custodial parent under the following
17 conditions:
18 1. The noncustodial parent fails to pay court ordered child
19 support for a consecutive three-month period.
20 2. The noncustodial parent purposely evades the court by
21 failing to accurately report income, and the custodial parent has
22 evidence of failure to disclose.
23
24
Req. No. 10367 Page 1
1 B. If courts find the noncustodial parent in violation of
2 Subsection A of this section, the court may order property and
3 assets to be seized in addition to requiring backpay.
4 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
